The whole process is quite cumbersome.
I suggest to start with the simplest client first â€“ &lt;code&gt;alpine&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Gotchas&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There's a &lt;a href="https://answers.uillinois.edu/illinois/page.php?id=85852"&gt;nice page at University of Illinois&lt;/a&gt; that describes how to configure &lt;code&gt;alpine&lt;/code&gt; for Office email.
I've been able to apply the configuration to at least read the inbound emails.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sending emails didn't work out of the box.
Hopefully, there's a &lt;a href="https://groups.google.com/g/comp.mail.pine/c/fKQT5l8qUog?pli=1"&gt;Google Groups&lt;/a&gt; thread about the dreaded:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mail not sent. Sending error: 250&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, when things go wrong, you might wanna make sure your sender name and sender email address match between the config file, the email header, and the email body.
Otherwise, sometimes you get weird errors.&lt;/p&gt;
